peopleAlsoAsk.question: How do I identify my crosscut saw?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Crosscut saws usually have two handles. Many vintage felling saws have one handle hole in each end. Bucking Saws—Bucking saws can be used for felling. Some saws were manufactured to try to incorporate the best characteristics of both types of saws.
